707341f-a.folder: West End Ave. & Hampton Ave., Brooklyn, NY
707341f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: West End Ave. - Hampton Ave.
707341f-a.text:
West End Ave., east side, between Hampton Ave., and Oriental Boulevard (street is in the background). The frame house to the left of the right of way in the background, is No. 120 West End Ave. The Long Island R.R. right of way is also seen. This area comprises of 12 acres, which extends north from Brighton Beach through to Neptune Ave, with frontage on Shore Ave. Upon this site which is near a fully developed community will be erected apartments and stores. For further information see the New York Sun,
February 11, 1937.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

707342f-a.text:
120 West End Ave.. (rear view shown) west side, south of Hampton Ave., showing at the extreme right No. 117 (no street) facing part of the Long Island R.P. right of way. To the left are a group of sheds, once a part of
the pumping station for this area.
December 1923.
Eurene L. Armbruster Collection.
